[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  rdfs:comment           "Note: RNAi experiment is not yet curated in WormBase. 2021-10-28" , "Supporting evidence statement (PMID:25429148): To detect a role for RTCB-1 in xbp-1 splicing, we performed RNAi knockdown of rtcb-1 in N2 worms and measured spliced (xbp-1s), unspliced (xbp-1u), and total (xbp-1t; i.e.,xbp-1s  xbp-1u) levels of xbp-1 mRNA, using real-time qPCR. Under tunicamycin-treated conditions, knockdown ofrtcb-1 significantly lowered xbp-1s and xbp-1t mRNA expression compared with control (Fig. 2A)." , "Supporting evidence statement (PMID:25429148): The rtcb-1\nmutant gk451 consists of a 370 bp deletion spanning the promoter and the first exon, most likely resulting in a nonfunctional protein.  rtcb-1 mutant animals were\ngrown until day 4 after hatching and exposed to tunicamycin (for 6 h) along with N2 control worms. Based on qPCR results, xbp-1s and xbp-1t mRNA expression was significantly reduced in rtcb-1 mutant worms compared with control animals (Fig. 2C). " ;
  lego:evidence          :6168d1e000001550 ;
  dc:contributor         "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196" ;
  dc:date                "2021-10-28" ;
  pav:providedBy         "http://www.wormbase.org" ;
  owl:annotatedProperty  obo:BFO_0000050 ;
  owl:annotatedSource    :5ce58dde00001438 ;
  owl:annotatedTarget    :614fa6f900001361
] .

